{"lemma":"صَوْمٌ","slug":"صَوْمٌ","root":"ص.#.م","root_slug":"ص-_-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-_-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَوْم","root":"صوم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25260"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَامَ (ṣāma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَامَ (ṣāma) (form I); fast, sawm (period of abstainment, usually from food and drink)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause to fast"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare with Hebrew צוֹם (ṣōm), Ge'ez ጾም (ṣom, “fast”), Ugaritic 𐎑𐎎 (ẓm, “fast”). Nöldeke was convinced that the meaning “to fast” is borrowed from the Aramaic צומא / ܨܰܘܡܳܐ (ṣōmā, ṣawmā, “fast”), referring to the verb’s meaning “to stand still”, Jeffery says that the Arabic verb is “obviously denominative from صَوْم (ṣawm)” and notes that the term is only used in late Qurʾānic passages. Cognate with Armenian ծոմ (com, “fast”) from Aramaic.\n\nVerb form II from the root ص و م (ṣ w m)."},"ipa":["/sˤawm/","/sˤaw.wa.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25260","headword_ar":"صَوْمٌ","root":"Swm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of 1 [q. v.]. (S, M, &c.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~awomu","text_ar":"الصَّوْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqotu AlS~awomi","text_ar":"وَقْتُ الصَّوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means also (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The month of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ramadán:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) whence the saying of Aboo-Zeyd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqamotu biAlbaSorapi Sawomayoni","text_ar":"اَقَمْتُ بِالبَصْرَةِ صَوْمَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I remained, stayed, dwelt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, in El-Basrah"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two Ramadáns."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawomN","text_ar":"صَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Christian church;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyEapN","text_ar":"بِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, TA:) as though for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHal~u AlS~awomi","text_ar":"مَحَلُّ الصَّوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwaqofi","text_ar":"الوَقْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for, as Hooker says, speaking of the ancient usage of the Church, “ their manner was to stand at prayer, whereupon their meetings unto that purpose had the names of stations given them ”]. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAy^imN","text_ar":"صَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dung of the ostrich."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.)       -A4-  And, in the dial. of Hudheyl, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) [but] the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the form of the figure of a human being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugly in appearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very much so, the fruits of which are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^uwsu Al$~ayaATiyni","text_ar":"رُوُوسُ الشَّيَاطِينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the serpents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoTaAnN","text_ar":"شَيْطَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaq~uwmN","text_ar":"زَقُّومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having leaves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AHn says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they have"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadab","text_ar":"هَدَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their branches do not spread forth, they grow in the manner of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species of tamarisk called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avol","text_ar":"اَثْل"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but are not so tall, and mostly grow in the districts of Benoo-Shebábeh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}